in the last two years.

131
00:05:47,592 --> 00:05:49,054
So to understand how all this happened,

132
00:05:49,634 --> 00:05:51,776
it's important to know the retro roots of both the game

133
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:53,437
and its previous competitive legacy.

134
00:05:54,078 --> 00:05:57,681
In 1989, Nintendo released their versions of Tetris

135
00:05:57,901 --> 00:05:59,523
for the 8-bit Nintendo Entertainment System

136
00:05:59,563 --> 00:06:00,083
and Game Boy.

137
00:06:00,584 --> 00:06:02,065
While these were not the earliest versions

138
00:06:02,105 --> 00:06:04,227
of the game released, they were the most widely distributed

139
00:06:04,287 --> 00:06:06,168
and heavily marketed versions of the game ever made

140
00:06:06,228 --> 00:06:08,410
and served as the first exposure of Tetris

141
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:09,731
for a generation of gamers.

142
00:06:10,352 --> 00:06:12,033
Tetris would then go on to become

143
00:06:12,054 --> 00:06:13,935
one of the most played and loved video games around the world,

144
00:06:13,975 --> 00:06:14,716
as you probably know.

145
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:19,192
In 1990, Nintendo launched the Nintendo World Championships

146
00:06:19,232 --> 00:06:19,893
in PowerFest.

147
00:06:20,293 --> 00:06:21,934
Featuring a stage show with giant screens

148
00:06:21,974 --> 00:06:23,355
and live announcers calling the action,

149
00:06:23,595 --> 00:06:25,076
this 30-city tour would challenge

150
00:06:25,196 --> 00:06:26,817
millions across the country and was

151
00:06:26,837 --> 00:06:29,138
the largest competitive gaming event held at the time.

152
00:06:29,738 --> 00:06:31,660
Loosely based on a fictitious competition

153
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,921
in the movie The Wizard, anybody remember that?

154
00:06:35,202 --> 00:06:37,503
Yeah, so it's like, yeah, Fred Savage.

155
00:06:38,764 --> 00:06:41,365
It featured a triathlon of games in which

156
00:06:41,445 --> 00:06:43,346
Tetris was the final and pivotal game that

157
00:06:43,386 --> 00:06:44,847
determined the outcome of the competition.

158
00:06:46,053 --> 00:06:48,314
As video games gained traction to become more mainstream

159
00:06:48,354 --> 00:06:50,855
in the 90s, this first NWC began an era

160
00:06:50,875 --> 00:06:53,156
where console manufacturers like Nintendo and Sega

161
00:06:53,697 --> 00:06:56,018
held massive multi-city competition tours

162
00:06:56,058 --> 00:06:58,899
where players of all ages could enter for free or low cost

163
00:06:59,239 --> 00:07:00,660
and play in a regional to qualify

164
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,020
for a national or world title.

165
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,141
Participants and champions of this era

166
00:07:04,221 --> 00:07:06,142
would later be involved in the interest behind

167
00:07:06,402 --> 00:07:08,783
and the formation of the classic Tetris World Championships.

168
00:07:10,384 --> 00:07:11,284
So decades passed.

169
00:07:11,653 --> 00:07:14,654
And as retro gaming rose in popularity along with the growth of the internet,

170
00:07:14,894 --> 00:07:18,055
it was found that many people were still interested in playing classic NES Tetris.

171
00:07:18,815 --> 00:07:22,156
Information and media such as gameplay videos began to surface.

172
00:07:22,537 --> 00:07:25,378
And in 2009, Harry Hong submitted a video which earned him

173
00:07:25,618 --> 00:07:30,679
the first Twin Galaxies maxed out score of 999,999 points.

174
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:33,620
This led to the production of a short film, But Harry,

175
00:07:34,161 --> 00:07:35,561
by filmmaker Adam Cornelius,

176
00:07:35,861 --> 00:07:38,842
and this led to more interest in finding other potential Tetris masters.

177
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:42,411
Because it seemed that after all of these years,

178
00:07:42,731 --> 00:07:45,773
one of the most iconic and widely loved games of all time

179
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:47,873
did not yet have an official champion.

180
00:07:48,414 --> 00:07:48,634
What?

181
00:07:51,175 --> 00:07:54,676
So, NWC 1990 competitor Robin Mahara

182
00:07:54,716 --> 00:07:56,097
teamed up with the filmmaker Adam

183
00:07:56,257 --> 00:07:58,598
and producer Vince Clemente to hold a competition

184
00:07:58,618 --> 00:08:00,058
to answer this unanswered question.

185
00:08:00,558 --> 00:08:02,399
Who is the best Tetris player in the world?

186
00:08:03,239 --> 00:08:03,599
On August 8, 2010,

187
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:06,120
the first Classic Tetris World Championship

188
00:08:06,381 --> 00:08:08,261
was held in the Downtown Independent Theater

189
00:08:08,281 --> 00:08:08,862
in Los Angeles.

190
00:08:09,278 --> 00:08:10,798
and we used the original NES console

191
00:08:10,838 --> 00:08:11,979
and the Tetris cartridge from 1989

192
